::USGOV-U01-L01-Q01::Which statement best explains the main purpose of government? {
~To remove all rules from society#Incorrect. Government exists to create structure, not remove all rules.
~To allow every person to make separate laws#Incorrect. Government creates shared laws for society rather than separate laws for each person.
=To maintain order, provide services, and make decisions for society#Correct. This matches the lesson focus on order, services, and decision-making.
~To prevent communities from working together#Incorrect. Government helps organize society and support cooperation.
}

::USGOV-U01-L01-Q02::Which example shows government providing a public service? {
~A student chooses a favorite hobby#Incorrect. A personal hobby is not a government service.
=A city maintains roads and transportation systems#Correct. Roads and transportation are examples of public services.
~A family decides what to cook for dinner#Incorrect. That is a private household decision, not a public service.
~A friend sends a text message#Incorrect. Sending a text is not a government service.
}

::USGOV-U01-L01-Q03::How does government help maintain order? {
=By creating and enforcing rules#Correct. The lesson explains that governments maintain order through rules and laws.
~By removing all laws and expectations#Incorrect. Removing laws would reduce order, not maintain it.
~By encouraging confusion in communities#Incorrect. Government is meant to organize society, not confuse it.
~By preventing all decisions from being made#Incorrect. Governments make decisions to help society function.
}

::USGOV-U01-L01-Q04::Why would society struggle without government? {
=There would likely be less structure and stability#Correct. The lesson explains that government provides structure, order, and stability.
~There would automatically be more fairness#Incorrect. The lesson does not suggest fairness increases automatically without government.
~There would be no need for public services#Incorrect. Public services are still necessary and are often organized by government.
~People would no longer need rules#Incorrect. Rules are still necessary for organized society.
}

::USGOV-U01-L01-Q05::Which statement is most accurate? {
~Government only exists to punish people#Incorrect. The lesson includes services and decision-making, not only punishment.
~Government has no effect on daily life#Incorrect. Government affects daily life through laws, services, and decisions.
~Government should never make decisions for communities#Incorrect. Governments do make decisions that affect communities.
=Government organizes society and helps communities function#Correct. This reflects the central idea of the lesson.
}
